{{Infobox person | name = Manuel Alejandro Grullón | image = Manuel A Grullon-v1.jpg | alt = | caption = | birth_name = Manuel Alejandro Grullón Viñas | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1953|05|09}} | birth_place = [[Santiago de los Caballeros]], [[Dominican Republic]] | death_date = <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} or {{Death-date and age|Month DD, YYYY|Month DD, YYYY}} (death date then birth date) --> | death_place = | nationality = Dominican | other_names = | known_for = | citizenship = | education = | alma_mater = {{flagicon|USA}} [[NYU]] | occupation = | years_active = | employer = | organization = Banco Popular | salary = | net_worth = | spouse = | partner = <!-- unmarried life partner; use ''Name (1950–present)'' --> | children = | parents = | relatives = | callsign = | awards = }}
'''Manuel Alejandro Grullón Viñas''' ([[Santiago de los Caballeros]], 9 May 1953) is a businessman from the [[Dominican Republic]]. In April 2014, he was appointed the Chairman of Grupo Popular, a company whose subsidiaries include {{Interlanguage link multi|Banco Popular Dominicano|es}}, the largest private bank in the Dominican Republic.<ref name=eldia>{{cite news|title=Don Alejandro Grullón le pasa la antorcha a su hijo Manuel en el Banco Popular|url=http://eldia.com.do/don-alejandro-grullon-le-pasa-la-antorcha-a-su-hijo-manuel-en-el-banco-popular/|accessdate=2 February 2015|agency=El Día|date=27 April 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150202104931/http://eldia.com.do/don-alejandro-grullon-le-pasa-la-antorcha-a-su-hijo-manuel-en-el-banco-popular/|archivedate=2 February 2015|location=Santo Domingo|language=Spanish}}</ref> He has been president of the Banco Popular Dominicano since 1990. ''[[Forbes]]'' listed Grullón as one of the ten wealthiest men of the Dominican Republic.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Leyba|first1=Nicanor|title=Los empresarios más ricos de República Dominicana|url=https://www.forbes.com.mx/los-empresarios-mas-ricos-de-republica-dominicana/|website=Forbes México|accessdate=15 May 2017|language=Spanish|date=24 February 2017}}</ref>
== Biography == Grullón was born to [[Alejandro Enrique Grullón Espaillat]] and Ana Dínorah Viñas Messina in 1953.{{cn|date=May 2017}} His father founded the Banco Popular Dominicano in August 1963, and held the position of President for 25 years.<ref>{{cite web|title=El día que fue inaugurado el Banco Popular Dominicano|url=http://www.diariodominicano.com/cultura/2014/08/23/177892/el-dia-que-fue-inaugurado-el-banco-popular-dominicano|website=Diario Dominicano|accessdate=15 May 2014|language=Spanish|date=23 August 2014}}</ref>
After completing his education in the United States, obtaining a degree in psychology from [[Tulane University]] and a master's degree in business administration from [[New York University]], Grullón returned to his home country, becoming involved in his father's company.<ref>{{cite web|title=People's Choice: Dominican Republic 2015|url=https://www.thebusinessyear.com/dominican-republic-2015/peoples-choice/interview|website=The Business Year|accessdate=15 May 2017}}</ref>
