{{Infobox newspaper | name = Äripäev | logo = Äripäev logo.svg | logo_size = 250px | image = | caption = | type = [[Daily newspaper|Daily]] | format = [[Berliner (format)|Berliner]] | owners = [[Bonnier Group]] | publisher = [[AS Äripäev]] | editor = | chiefeditor = Meelis Mandel | assoceditor = | maneditor = Igor Rõtov | newseditor = | managingeditordesign = | campuseditor = | campuschief = | opeditor = | sportseditor = | photoeditor = | staff = | foundation = {{Start date|df=yes|1989}} | political = | language = [[Estonian language|Estonian]] | ceased publication = | headquarters = [[Tallinn]], [[Estonia]] | circulation = | sister newspapers = | ISSN = 1406-2585 | oclc = | website = [http://www.ap3.ee www.ap3.ee] }} '''''Äripäev''''' ([[Estonian language|Estonian]] for "Business Day") is an [[Estonia]]n financial [[newspaper]] in tabloid format. It was founded in 1989<ref name=eur>{{cite book|title=Central and South-Eastern Europe 2004|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=5J_gAU8c9NIC&pg=PA263|accessdate=4 June 2016|year=2003|publisher=Psychology Press|isbn=978-1-85743-186-5|page=263}}</ref> by ''[[Dagens Industri]]'', a leading Swedish financial [[newspaper]]. The first issue of ''Äripäev'' was published on 9 October 1989. Until May 1992 ''Äripäev'' was published once a week, until February 1996 three times a week. Since 1996 ''Äripäev'' has been published five times a week.<ref name="eur"/>
The newspaper belongs to AS Äripäev, which is owned by the Swedish family-owned media group [[Bonnier Group|Bonnier]].
